result.execSummary:
This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
2:27 PM; Case called for Hearing.  Defendant Aniya A Woods in court.  Prosecuting attorney Andrea M Will in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Court reviews the case and inquires if the defendant plans to retain counsel.  Defendant advises that she did not qualify for a public defender and she needs additional time to retain private counsel.  Court also advises that the defendant may also petition the court for an attorney as well.  Court will adjourn for further proceedings/status of counsel in about 30 days.
Hearing scheduled for November 28, 2022 at 10:30 am.

Defendant to comply with I.D. Processing.  Defendant is not to possess any dangerous weapons/firearms. Defendant is not to use/possess any controlled substances without a valid prescription and take as prescribed. Defendant not to possess any drug paraphernalia.  Absolute sobriety, defendant is not to possess or consume any alcohol.

10:08 AM Defendant Aniya A Woods in court. District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin by Niki Kane.  Defense acknowledges receipt of complaint and waives reading of complaint. Service admitted/advised of charges and potential penalties. Court advises of right to an attorney.  Defendant to apply at Public Defender's Office for representation.  NOT GUILTY PLEA ENTERED BY COURT.
Hearing scheduled for October 27, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
State's Demand for Discovery and Inspection and Notice of Intent to Use Defendant's Statement and DNA Evidence.
